  "description": "The lead is the first card played that opens a comparative unit, commonly a [trick](./trick.md), in a [card game](../index.md). The player who leads sets the [suit](./suit.md) or category that subsequent players must [follow](./follow-suit.md), establishing the frame within which the trick is contested.",
